modules.description: This module defines error types and helper functions for handling JSON parsing errors. It works with string and error type values to report issues like type mismatches or malformed variants during JSON deserialization. Concrete use cases include validating JSON structure when decoding custom data types and providing clear error messages for invalid inputs.

This module converts JSON values to OCaml types like int32, float, string, and bool, handling different JSON representations during parsing and serialization. It includes functions such as make_bool and make_int to construct JSON values from OCaml primitives, supporting use cases like decoding JSON into typed records or lists. The error-handling submodule defines types and helpers for reporting parsing issues such as type mismatches or malformed variants, enabling robust validation of JSON structure. Together, these components allow precise conversion and error-resilient processing of JSON data in OCaml.
